{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Problem\n`src/rebar/config.py` is 869 LOC тАФ over the 800-LOC module-size soft cap тАФ and is grandfathered in `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt` + `.github/module-size-ceilings.txt` (pinned 869), with a remedy row in `docs/architecture.md`.\n\n## arch.md remedy row is STALE / already-shipped\nThe `docs/architecture.md` offenders row for `config.py` reads \"split the dataclass/schema from the env/CLI-override + cache machinery along the existing seam\". That seam ALREADY SHIPPED: the typed dataclass/schema layer now lives in the sibling `src/rebar/_config_schema.py` (config.py already imports `_SECTIONS`, `Config`, `ConfigError`, `_as_bool`, `coerce_sparse`, `merge_sparse` from it). So the recorded remedy no longer describes an available seam тАФ it is superseded. This ticket DELETES that stale row rather than claiming it records the seam below.\n\n## New seam (on the CURRENT code): raw-input source layer\nExtract the raw-input resolution layer тАФ filesystem config discovery + TOML file parsing (with the mtime-keyed parse cache) + `REBAR_*` env & legacy-alias override collection тАФ into a NEW leaf `src/rebar/_config_sources.py`. This cluster is cohesive (it turns files+env into raw sparse mappings) and sits strictly BELOW the typed-merge/cache/precedence machinery that stays in config.py (`load_config`, `_ordered_layers`, `_resolve`, the resolved-Config cache, the public writers/readers).\n\nMOVE (by name): `repo_root`, `config_file`, `tracker_dir_override`, `_TOML_CACHE`, `_parse_toml`, `_read_toml_table`, `_pyproject_rebar_state`, `_discover_project_config`, `user_config_path`, `_CANONICAL_ENV_NAMES`, `_canonical_env_name`, `_LEGACY_ENV_ALIASES`, `_map_legacy_env`, `env_overrides`, `_strict_unknown_keys`.\n\nThe leaf imports ONLY stdlib + `rebar._config_schema` + `rebar._deprecations` (no import of `rebar.config`), so it is a true leaf with no back-edge.\n\n## Back-compat (public surface preserved)\nconfig.py RE-EXPORTS the full moved set (`from rebar._config_sources import X as X`), so `rebar.config.<name>` attribute access and `from rebar.config import <name>` keep resolving unchanged (~90 importers; externally-used include `repo_root`, `tracker_dir_override`, `_canonical_env_name`, `_LEGACY_ENV_ALIASES`, `user_config_path`, `_read_toml_table`, `_discover_project_config`, `env_overrides`). Two invariants preserved:\n- `_TOML_CACHE` shared-object identity: `reset_config_cache` stays in config.py and mutates the imported dict via `.clear()` (never rebinds) тАФ test_config_perf.py depends on this.\n- Monkeypatch seam: retained callers (`_ordered_layers` etc.) call the BARE re-exported names (`_discover_project_config(...)`), so `monkeypatch.setattr(cfg, \"_discover_project_config\", ...)` still intercepts resolution.\n\n## Scope note\nThis is a pure/mechanical refactor: NO signature or logic changes. E5 testing-plan is not-applicable тАФ the existing config test suite (test_config_perf, test_config_loader, test_config_surface_golden, test_config_backcompat, test_config_tracker_dir, test_config_show) is the behavioral oracle.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] New leaf `src/rebar/_config_sources.py` exists with a line count in [100, 800]; verify: `n=$(wc -l < src/rebar/_config_sources.py); [ \"$n\" -ge 100 ] && [ \"$n\" -le 800 ]`\n- [ ] `src/rebar/config.py` is at most 800 lines; verify: `[ \"$(wc -l < src/rebar/config.py)\" -le 800 ]`\n- [ ] config.py removed from the allowlist; verify: `grep -qv \"src/rebar/config.py\" .github/module-size-allowlist.txt && ! grep -q \"src/rebar/config.py\" .github/module-size-allowlist.txt`\n- [ ] config.py removed from the ceilings file; verify: `! grep -q \"src/rebar/config.py\" .github/module-size-ceilings.txt`\n- [ ] The stale config.py remedy row is gone from docs/architecture.md; verify: `! grep -q \"config.py.*split the dataclass/schema\" docs/architecture.md`\n- [ ] Module-size contract test passes (allowlist == over-cap set == ceilings keys); verify: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_module_size_contract.py -q`\n- [ ] Config test suite passes; verify: `python -m pytest tests/unit -k config -q`\n- [ ] Lint clean; verify: `make lint` reports \"All checks passed!\""}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784398549589392001,"uuid":"2591ad74-6b95-40e0-a32e-b80d22b5a129"}